  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "Add Zoom Chat Integration with Multi-Tenant Support\n\nImplement a Zoom Chat integration that captures all direct messages and channel messages in real-time via Zoom Marketplace OAuth app, persisting them to a dedicated database table with full multi-tenant isolation.\n\nPrerequisites:\n- Zoom Marketplace OAuth app created with User-managed type\n- OAuth scopes approved: chat_message:read, chat_channel:read\n- Webhook endpoint publicly accessible (via existing infrastructure)\n- Multi-tenant architecture patterns followed from existing Crisp and Gmail integrations\n\nDatabase:\n- Create a new zoom_chat_messages table in Neon Postgres with columns for: id, organization_id (tenant), zoom_user_id, message_id, channel_id, channel_type (DM vs channel), sender_id, sender_name, message_content, timestamp, raw_payload, created_at\n- Add appropriate indexes on organization_id, zoom_user_id, and timestamp for query performance\n- Store OAuth credentials (access_token, refresh_token, expiry) per tenant in the existing integrations table or a new zoom_oauth_tokens table\n\nOAuth Flow:\n- Add Zoom as a new integration option on the existing admin integrations setup page\n- Implement OAuth 2.0 authorization flow with redirect URI handling\n- Store and refresh tokens per tenant automatically\n- Handle token expiry and re-authorization gracefully\n\nWebhook Endpoint:\n- Create a POST endpoint to receive chat_message.sent events from Zoom\n- Validate incoming webhook payloads using Zoom's verification token or request signature\n- Parse and persist DM messages and channel messages, tagging each record with the correct organization_id\n- Return 200 response immediately to prevent Zoom retries, process asynchronously if needed\n\nMessage Ingestion:\n- Support both DM (peer-to-peer) and channel message types\n- Capture sender metadata, channel context, and full message content\n- Handle Zoom's pagination if backfilling historical messages via GET /v2/chat/users/me/messages\n- Deduplicate messages using Zoom's message_id to prevent double-ingestion on webhook retries\n\nEdge Cases to Handle:\n- Webhook signature verification failures should return 403 and log the attempt\n- Edited or deleted messages should update or soft-delete existing records\n- Token refresh failures should trigger an admin alert and pause ingestion gracefully\n- Rate limits on the Zoom REST API during any backfill operations",
  "title": "Implement Zoom Chat integration with multi-tenant support",
